<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="258" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognized among species of 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[672,993,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cantharocoris">
<emphasis box="[672,804,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Schizoptera</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[822,984,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Cantharocoris</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the dark brown coloration and light brown wing membrane; sternum 6 with a broad and rounded posterior process (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1153,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
, black arrow); subgenital plate with a tiny process with bifid tip (
<figureCitation box="[586,702,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
, white arrow); right conjunctival appendage elongate and slender, with distal portion bearing tiny spine-like projections (
<figureCitation box="[763,881,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
), left conjunctival appendage short and plate-like (
<figureCitation box="[159,278,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
), right paramere very long and curved, with narrowed distal portion, left paramere with enlarged base and narrowed and a strongly curved distal portion (
<figureCitation box="[723,843,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="258" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,418,366,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[438,543,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-217@3.[151,1436,597,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Corixidea graziae sp. nov., Corixidea quilombola sp. nov., and Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691704/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 2</figureCitation>
): macropterous, body ovate. Coloration: generally dark brown, light brown membrane, Sc+C distinctly lighter than the remainder of hemelytra, legs yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1095,1366,402,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Surface and vestiture:</emphasis>
head, pronotum, and wing veins covered with long, light brown setae; several circular muscle scars on head; abdomen densely covered with elongate setae. Structure: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[692,765,475,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Head:</emphasis>
triangular in frontal view, synthlipsis about three times the width of the eye. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[344,442,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Thorax:</emphasis>
posterior pronotal margin weakly concave medially, scutellum triangular, with a rounded tip, hind coxa with well-developed adhesive pad, tarsal formula 3-3-3. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[926,1052,546,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Sternum 6 with a pigmented broad and rounded posterior process, sternum 7 with a pigmented broad and rounded process in the anterolateral corner of the left side, subgenital plate with a tiny process with bifid tip posteriorly directed (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1215,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1235,1345,618,644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1822,1846]" captionTargetBox="[169,1429,604,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-109@5.[151,1436,597,1798]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalic features. A. Corixidea graziae sp. nov. B. Corixidea quilombola sp. nov. C–D. Schizoptera (Cantharocoris) savannensis sp. nov. C. Ventral view of abdominal apex; black arrow points to posterior process of sternum 6 and white arrow points to lateral process of subgenital plate. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: lca = left conjunctival appendage, lp = left paramere, rca = right conjunctival appendage, rp = right paramere, st6 = sternum 6, st7 = sternum 7 (subgenital plate), mt8 = mediotergite 8, mt8p = mediotergite 8 process, py = pygophore, v = vesica. Scale bars: A–B = 0.1 mm, B–C = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4691708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4691708/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
): Right conjunctival appendage elongate and slender, with distal portion bearing tiny spine-like projections; left conjunctival appendage short and plate-like; right paramere very long and curved, with narrowed distal portion; left paramere with enlarged base and narrowed and strongly curved distal portion; vesica very long, looping, moderately slender, with 2–3 coils.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1242,799,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1113]" box="[199,1242,799,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the savanna environment where the type-specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,542,834,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1113]" box="[199,542,834,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,834,860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,427,835,861]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[443,530,835,861]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Amapá</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="258" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,871,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species differs from all other described species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1286,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cantharocoris">
<emphasis box="[1124,1286,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Cantharocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the following combination of features: sternum 6 with a pigmented broad and rounded posterior process, sternum 7 with a pigmented broad and rounded process in the anterolateral corner of left side, and subgenital plate with tiny process with bifid tip. 
<taxonomicName authority="Emsley, 1969" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[322,896,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandi" subGenus="Cantharocoris">
<emphasis box="[322,454,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Schizoptera</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[474,636,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Cantharocoris</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[656,731,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">grandi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Emsley, M. G." box="[741,896,979,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref4419" refString="Emsley, M. G. (1969) The Schizopteridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) with the descriptions of new species from Trinidad. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society, 25, 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="1969">Emsley, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Emsley, 1969" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1969" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apatosulcata" subGenus="Cantharocoris">
<emphasis box="[958,1090,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Schizoptera</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1110,1272,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Cantharocoris</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1292,1437,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">apatosulcata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Emsley, M. G." box="[151,309,1015,1041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="258" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref4419" refString="Emsley, M. G. (1969) The Schizopteridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) with the descriptions of new species from Trinidad. Memoirs of the American Entomological Society, 25, 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="1969">Emsley, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both from 
<collectingCountry box="[444,666,1015,1041]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="6" pageNumber="258">Trinidad &amp; Tobago</collectingCountry>
, also have subgenital plate with the process with bifid tip, but it is anteriorly directed, while in the new species the process is posteriorly directed. However, the sterna 6 and 7 of these species lack the pigmented broad and rounded process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
